Coding convention 

Variables name                          -                   underscore style (e.g. int obj_counter)
Function name                           -                   Start with _ if not an API function (e.g. _get_obj_counter(), read())
tabs                                    -                   4 spaces
Function comments                       -                   Comments above every major function

e.g:
/*
 * dci_create_container
 * It first finds the matching node of provided cloud plugin, then creates a 
 * container of given name.
 *
 * Input:
 * int - pointer holding address of cloud plugin.
 * char * - pointer holding container name.
 *
 * Output:
 * int - 0 on success, non-zero on failure.
 */
dci_error_t dci_create_container(int dcid, char *cid);
    
Todo                                    -                   Write /*FIXME*/ in front of everything that needs to be fixed or is a todo
Distinguish between data manipulation and algorithm

